  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      SYSTEMIC INFLAMMATION HAS BEEN ASSOCIATED WITH SEVERE COVID-19. HYPONATREMIA CAN RESULT FROM
      INFLAMMATION DUE TO NON-OSMOTIC STIMULI FOR VASOPRESSIN PRODUCTION. IN THIS PROSPECTIVE
      COHORT STUDY WE ANALIZED DATA FROM PATIENTS WITH COVID-19 AND THE ASOCIATION WITH
      HYPONATREMIA AND CLINICAL OUTCOMES.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
